. They would be able to improve the quality of software releases and reduce the risk of introducing defects into production. Security Engineers would gain valuable skills in code scanning, secret scanning, and dependency management, enabling them to identify and mitigate security vulnerabilities in the software supply chain. They would be able to implement automated security checks and maintain secure GitHub repositories. Therefore, the training would be beneficial to software developers, DevOps engineers, software architects, system administrators, project managers, QA engineers, and security engineers."
